OL,4,Cplane but denied compensation
OL,6,FThe Civil Aviation Act was updated in
OL,7,F1996 to ensure criminal acts on
OL,8,Fforeign planes bound for the UK can be
OL,9,Fprosecuted in UK criminal courts,
OL,10,Fwhich meant that Jussab could be
OL,11,Farrested and charged when the plane
OL,12,Flanded in Gatwick.
OL,14,FBut victims in these cases, like
OL,15,FKelly, still cannot be compensated.
OL,17,FLaw firm Leigh Day, which is
OL,18,Frepresenting Kelly, has written to
OL,19,FJustice Secretary Shabana Mahmood,
OL,20,Furging her to close what it believes
OL,21,Fis a gap in the law.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
